tafsir[7]{c,v,t}:
  37,107,"And I set Ishmael free in exchange for a huge ram which was to be slaughtered instead of him."
  37,108,"I preserved good praise for Abraham to remain among the following nations."
  37,114,"And verily I favoured Moses and his brother Aaron with messengership."
  37,117,"I gave Moses and his brother Aaron the Torah; a clear book from Allah in which there was no doubt."
  37,118,"I also guided them towards the straight path in which there was no deviance. It was the path of the religion of Islam which led to the pleasure of the Creator (may He be glorified)."
  37,119,"And I also preserved for them positive mention and good praise among the following nations."
  37,125,"“Do you worship your idol Ba‘l instead of Allah and leave the worship of Allah who is the best of creators?”"